# Pluto Experiment Tracking

Pluto is the experiment tracking library used in this project. When generating or modifying ML training code, follow these API patterns.

## Core Workflow

```python
import pluto

config = {"learning_rate": 0.001, "epochs": 10, "batch_size": 32}

run = pluto.init(
    project="<project-name>",
    name="<run-name>",        # optional
    config=config,
    tags=["experiment", "v1"],  # optional
)

try:
    for epoch in range(config["epochs"]):
        # ... training ...
        run.log({
            "train/loss": train_loss,
            "val/loss": val_loss,
            "epoch": epoch,
        })
finally:
    run.finish()
```

## Key Rules

- `pluto.init()` returns an `Op` object — assign to `run` or `op`
- `run.log()` takes a dict: keys are metric names, values are numeric or Pluto data types
- Use `/`-separated metric names for dashboard grouping: `"train/loss"`, `"val/loss"`
- Always call `run.finish()` — use `try/finally` for safety
- Import is `import pluto`, NOT `import mlop` (deprecated)

## PyTorch Integration

```python
run = pluto.init(project="my-project", config=config)
model = MyModel()
run.watch(model)  # tracks gradients, parameters, architecture
# ... training loop with run.log() ...
run.finish()
```

## PyTorch Lightning

```python
from pluto.compat.lightning import MLOPLogger

logger = MLOPLogger(project="my-project", config=config, tags=["lightning"])
trainer = pl.Trainer(logger=logger)
trainer.fit(model, train_dl, val_dl)
# finish() is automatic
```

## HuggingFace Transformers

```python
import pluto
from pluto.compat.transformers import PlutoCallback

run = pluto.init(project="my-project", config=config)
trainer = Trainer(model=model, args=args, callbacks=[PlutoCallback()])
trainer.train()
run.finish()
```

## Media & Data Types

```python
run.log({"image": pluto.Image(data=array, caption="sample")})
run.log({"audio": pluto.Audio(data=waveform, sample_rate=22050)})
run.log({"video": pluto.Video(path="./episode.mp4")})
run.log({"text": pluto.Text(data="model output text")})
run.log({"checkpoint": pluto.Artifact(path="model.pt", name="best")})
run.log({"weights": pluto.Histogram(data=param.detach().cpu().numpy())})
run.log({"results": pluto.Table(columns=["pred", "actual"], data=[...])})
```

All media types accept `data=` (in-memory) or `path=` (file). Use `caption=` for labels.

## DDP / Distributed

- Set a shared `run_id` across ranks so all log to the same run
- `run.finish()` auto-detects DDP and uses non-blocking shutdown
- No `if __name__ == "__main__":` guard needed

## Tags

```python
run = pluto.init(project="p", tags=["sweep", "v2"])
run.add_tags("high-accuracy")
run.remove_tags("old-tag")
```

## Config Updates

```python
run.update_config({"early_stop_epoch": epoch, "best_val_loss": best_loss})
```
